cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with automatic phonemic transcription, which is a subfield of natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with acoustic modeling. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a customized acoustic model to predict phoneme distributions. The paper also involves the use of zero-shot learning, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with language documentation for low-resource languages.
